I like how tactile and physical the phones are in this movie. The internet is often portrayed as something abstract as "the cloud" in movies (even the Social Network falls into this trap), so I appreciate any movie that gets into the nitty gritty of web servers. The annoying hum of these crappy plastic phones and the loud internet dial up sounds are such good details and make the ending so much more impactful.
